maxiofs (1:1.1.0) stable; urgency=medium

  * Release v1.1.0 - AWS S3 UI overhaul, S3 compatibility improvements, and security fixes
  * [UI] Actions toolbar in bucket browser: replaced per-row action buttons with a single AWS S3-style
    Actions dropdown operating on checkbox-selected items. Supports Copy S3 URI, Copy URL, Download,
    Download as ZIP, Calculate Folder Size, Share, Presigned URL, View Versions, Legal Hold, Rename,
    Edit Tags, and Delete. Actions disabled automatically based on selection type and count.
  * [UI] Object detail view: clicking a file now opens a full-page detail view (Properties, Permissions,
    Versions tabs) with copy-to-clipboard buttons, lazy-loaded ACL and version history, and a breadcrumb
    with clickable segments.
  * [UI] Bucket browser breadcrumb: replaced "Back to Buckets" button with inline breadcrumb
    (Buckets > bucket > folder) and dynamic page title showing current folder name.
  * [UI] Object rename via Actions menu: copies data+metadata+tags to new key, deletes original.
    Blocked for objects under COMPLIANCE retention or active Legal Hold.
  * [UI] Object tags editor via Actions menu: view and edit S3 object tags inline.
  * [UI] Folder download as ZIP: streams up to 10,000 objects / 10 GB as a ZIP archive without
    buffering server-side; limits enforced before streaming begins.
  * [UI] Folder size calculator via Actions menu: totals size and object count under a prefix.
  * [S3] GetObjectAttributes: returns ETag, StorageClass, ObjectSize, and part count without body.
    Required by AWS CLI v2, SDK v3, and Mountpoint S3.
  * [S3] PublicAccessBlock enforcement: IgnorePublicAcls/RestrictPublicBuckets flags now consulted
    before ACL evaluation (previously stored but never checked).
  * [S3] Real GetBucketLogging/PutBucketLogging: access log entries buffered and delivered
    asynchronously to the target bucket in AWS S3 access log format.
  * [S3] PutObject conditional write (If-None-Match: *): returns 412 PreconditionFailed if object
    exists. Required by Terraform state backends and distributed lock managers.
  * [S3] Real GetBucketEncryption/PutBucketEncryption/DeleteBucketEncryption: persistent SSE
    configuration per bucket; previously always returned 404.
  * [Fixed] Global encryption not applied when bucket had no explicit SSE rule set.
  * [Fixed] x-amz-server-side-encryption response header missing on GetObject/HeadObject/PutObject.
  * [Fixed] SigV2 HMAC used SHA256+hex instead of SHA1+base64; all V2 presigned URLs rejected.
  * [Fixed] SigV2 CanonicalizedResource omitted sub-resource query params (versionId, acl, etc.).
  * [Fixed] Bucket policy Condition blocks silently skipped; implemented full condition evaluator
    (StringEquals, StringLike, IpAddress/CIDR, Bool, Numeric, Arn operators).
  * [Fixed] Bucket policy Principal null granted access to all users.
  * [Fixed] DeleteBucket bypassed Object Lock on versioned buckets via /.versions/ path detection.
  * [Fixed] Console port (8081) missing all security headers (CSP, X-Frame-Options, nosniff).
  * [Fixed] InternalError responses leaked internal filesystem paths.
  * [Fixed] 3 data races: metrics collector running flag, handleTrace goroutine, SSE test recorder.
  * [Fixed] Object detail view: delete triggered back-navigation before confirmation modal resolved.
  * [Fixed] tenantId not forwarded to ACL, versions, versions modal, presigned URL modal.
  * [Fixed] Object detail view breadcrumb segments all navigated to bucket root instead of prefix.
  * [Fixed] Object detail view tab/field labels hardcoded in Spanish; full i18n applied.
  * [Changed] Go and npm dependencies updated to latest versions.

