maxiofs (1.0.0-rc1) unstable; urgency=high

  * Release v1.0.0-rc1 - First release candidate: comprehensive security audit, AES-256-GCM
    authenticated encryption, CSR-based cluster TLS, SSRF hardening across all outbound HTTP
  * [Security CRITICAL] AES-256-CTR replaced with AES-256-GCM for object encryption.
    CTR provided no authentication tag — attacker with storage access could flip bits silently.
    GCM uses 64 KB authenticated chunks; tampering is detected on read. Backward-compatible:
    existing CTR objects decrypted transparently on first access.
  * [Security CRITICAL] Cluster CA private key no longer transmitted during node join.
    CSR-based flow: joining node generates its own key pair, sends only a CSR, CA signs it.
  * [Security HIGH] 6 cluster handlers missing isGlobalAdmin check — any authenticated user
    could initialize, join, or dismantle the cluster. All 6 handlers now enforce admin role.
  * [Security HIGH] SSRF protection added to notification webhooks, HTTP logging targets,
    and replication destination endpoints (blocks RFC 1918, loopback, link-local).
  * [Security HIGH] Path traversal via backslash on Windows filesystem backend.
  * [Security HIGH] Replication credentials now encrypted at rest (AES-256-GCM).
  * [Security HIGH] HMAC nonce replaced with crypto/rand (was time.Now().UnixNano()).
  * [Security HIGH] Infinite cluster proxy loop prevented via X-MaxIOFS-Proxied header.
  * [Security MEDIUM] OAuth CSRF state validation added to Google callback.
  * [Security MEDIUM] CORS wildcard origin replaced with explicit allowlist.
  * [Security MEDIUM] Multipart upload capped at 10,000 parts (DoS prevention).
  * [Security MEDIUM] Frontend auth cookies now include Secure and SameSite=Strict flags.
  * [Security MEDIUM] HTML sanitizer rewritten — entity decoding, URL attribute allowlist.
  * [Security MEDIUM] XSS: server values now escaped before HTML template interpolation.
  * [Changed] Frontend JS bundle reduced 45% via React.lazy code splitting (1,003→550 kB).
  * [Changed] Accessibility: aria-current, aria-label, aria-expanded on nav and icon buttons.
  * [Changed] Debian/RPM packages now auto-restart service after upgrade if it was running.
  * [Fixed] Mobile sidebar overlay stays open after navigating to a page.

