maxiofs (1.0.0-beta) unstable; urgency=high

  * Release v1.0.0-beta - First major release: Pebble engine, object integrity, maintenance mode,
    SMTP alerts, cluster resilience, full i18n, audit object events, async audit writes
  * [Changed] Replaced BadgerDB with Pebble (github.com/cockroachdb/pebble) for all S3 metadata.
    Pebble uses a crash-safe WAL — no more MANIFEST corruption on power loss or process kill.
    Pure-Go, no CGO, same LSM-tree paradigm, identical on-disk key format preserved.
  * [Changed] Transparent auto-migration: on first startup, KEYREGISTRY detection triggers
    full BadgerDB→Pebble migration in batches. Atomic directory rename. No user action needed.
  * [Changed] Decoupled ACL, bucket, object, metrics, notifications from BadgerDB via new
    metadata.RawKVStore interface. Only migration code retains BadgerDB dependency.
  * [Changed] Removed LZ4/Snappy compression (minimal benefit, added latency for compressed content)
  * [Changed] Full i18n coverage: cluster, metrics, buckets, settings, auth pages translated (en/es)
  * [Added] Object Integrity Verification: on-demand + background scrubber, corruption SSE+email alerts
  * [Added] Maintenance Mode enforcement: S3 API (HTTP 503) and Console API middleware, amber banner
  * [Added] SMTP email notifications: 3-mode TLS (none/starttls/ssl), test endpoint, settings UI
  * [Added] Disk and quota alert monitoring: SSE + email on threshold escalation (80%/90%)
  * [Added] Disk/quota alert auto-resolution: condition-based notifications dismiss when resolved
  * [Added] Cluster state snapshot + Stale Reconciler (LWW conflict resolution for partitioned nodes)
  * [Added] Background stats reconciler: recalculates ObjectCount/TotalSize every 15 minutes
  * [Added] Admin endpoint POST /buckets/{bucket}/recalculate-stats
  * [Added] Non-blocking bulk delete with real-time progress bar (8 concurrent workers)
  * [Added] Audit: object operation events (uploaded, downloaded, deleted, shared) from Console API
  * [Added] Audit: structured forwarding to external log targets at Info level with "audit":true tag
  * [Added] Metrics: immediate startup snapshot (no chart gap on server start)
  * [Added] Cluster: object_count and total_size per bucket in cluster buckets endpoint
  * [Fixed] Audit SQLite SQLITE_BUSY under concurrent load: async batched writer goroutine + WAL mode
  * [Fixed] Large file multipart upload: 5 cascading bugs (error type, Windows rename race,
    excessive I/O 3x, Flusher propagation, goroutine context cancellation on client disconnect)
  * [Fixed] Virtual-hosted-style S3 requests (bucket in subdomain): transparent URL rewrite middleware
  * [Fixed] Bucket object count inflation on overwrite (AdjustBucketSize, no ObjectCount increment)
  * [Fixed] Bucket metrics under-reported under concurrent load (sync.Mutex replaces OCC retry loop)
  * [Fixed] RecalculateBucketStats ignored tenant prefix, always returning 0 for tenant buckets
  * [Fixed] Metrics chart false spikes from stale query data (30s staleness guard)
  * [Fixed] Empty folders not displayed in object browser (delimiter-based folder marker handling)
  * [Fixed] Regular users locked out of own profile and access keys (isSelf exception)
  * [Fixed] SSE notification stream erroneously opened by non-admin users
  * [Fixed] Bucket permissions modal allowing cross-scope grants (strict tenant isolation)

